OL,6,FBenton was , offering to lobby
OL,7,Fministers and table parliamentary
OL,8,Fquestions on behalf of gambling
OL,9,Finvestors.
OL,11,FFootage also showed him allegedly
OL,12,Fboasting there were ways to keep
OL,13,Fcorporate hospitality secret.
OL,15,FHe appeared to suggest MPs allow
OL,16,Fcompanies to put a falsely low value
OL,17,Fon tickets they have accepted for live
OL,18,Fsports and cultural events, in order
OL,19,Fto avoid the requirement to disclose
OL,20,Fhospitality worth #300 or more.
